        <div class="commentcontent">
            <blockquote>But are they seedless?</blockquote>
I'd think not. To most of the people I've talked to here, seedless watermelons sound completely alien.

<p>While fruit is always expensive here, there is plenty of obscenely-priced fruit for use as gifts even in regular supermarkets, e.g. a rather small box of big blue grapes that usually goes for ~USD 80.</p>
		</div>
	</div>



        
    
        
